The paper discusses the challenges of preserving data trustworthiness in the context of Mobile Crowd-Sensing applications (MCS) using IoT data. This involves assessing the effectiveness and accuracy of data mining algorithms for IoT security and privacy. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper deals with data analysis and information extraction. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with spatio-temporal changes and concept drifts, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of large datasets, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
